news.title: Goa: GWMC secures patent for laterite-based concrete block
news.para: The laterite-based concrete block will result in a cleaner environment and less contamination of soil and groundwater, a senior GWMC officer said.

news.title: Thailand’s economy expects 4% growth in 2024 driven by property sector: Finance Ministry
news.para: The measures are expected to lead to about 800 billion baht ($22 billion) in property trades, more than 400 billion baht in investment and 120 billion baht in consumption, Pornchai Thiraveja, head of the ministry's fiscal policy office, told a briefing.

news.title: Ajmera Realty & Infra reports 21% increase in sales booking in FY24
news.para: In a regulatory filing, the Mumbai-based firm said that the sales booking in carpet area rose 28 per cent to 4,72,751 square feet during 2023-24 fiscal from 3,70,219 square feet in the previous year.

news.title: Calcutta HC directs civic body to suspend erring officials for Garden Reach building collapse
news.para: The court said that it would take a call on a prayer by the petitioner for CBI investigation into the matter if the local police do not hold the probe in a bonafide manner and "do not lift the veil over the public servants who appear to be conveniently somnolent."

news.title: SRE Group sells 51% stake in Shanghai Jinxin Property for $472 million
news.para: The company is selling its stake in Shanghai Jinxin Property to a China-based real estate developer Zhongchong Investment Group, it said in a statement.

news.title: Lucknow development body seals row houses in Chinhat
news.para: “The sealing drive against illegal construction is done on the order of courts. People should avoid such construction to refrain from sealing of their buildings,” said Indramani Tripathi, VC, LDA.

news.title: Over 1,000 apartments lack occupancy certificates in Bhubaneswar
news.para: As per the data, there are about 1,116 residential buildings registered with the Odisha Real Estate Regulatory Authority (ORERA) so far out of which only 55 buildings have got the OCs, which does not consist of even 5% of the total registered buildings.

news.title: Godrej Properties reports 84% increase in sales booking in FY24
news.para: Macrotech Developers has reported sales of Rs 14,520 crore in the previous fiscal. DLF is yet to announce its numbers, These four listed entities are in the race to gain market share.

news.title: Bidhannagar civic body seeks cop help to raze 20 illegal buildings
news.para: “A letter has been sent to the police to raze the structures at one go,” said an official. In the past nine months, BMC has issued a total of 174 stop-work orders and lodged 30 FIRs against illegal constructions.

news.title: Brihanmumbai civic body imposes double property tax penalty for Marathi Signboard violation
news.para: The Supreme Court had given two months for displaying Marathi language or Devanagari script on signboards in shops and establishments before the November 23, 2023, deadline.

news.title: Skyway project to affect 100 Shamirpet properties in Secunderabad Cantonment
news.para: “The land acquisition process has to be initiated under Transfer of Development Rights (TDR),” according to orders (a copy of which is in TOI’s possession) issued by the HMDA commissioner, who was also the MA&UD principal secretary, M Dana Kishore.

news.title: Panvel civic body collects property tax worth Rs 360 crore in FY24
news.para: PCMC’s property tax collection from 2016 to 2024 stands at 647 crore, which includes the last fiscal year’s record collection of Rs 360 crore.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh housing department's revenue up 1.75 times in FY24
news.para: Generating Rs 12,738 crore for the state coffers the Awas Vikas Parishad (UP housing board) collected the maximum amount followed by LDA.

news.title: CPCB and HSPCB conduct checks on brick kilns in Haryana
news.para: The inspections of the Hisar brick kilns, carried out between March 2023 and Feb this year, focused on various aspects such as location, implementation of zig-zag technology, monitoring provisions, and the type of fuel being used.

news.title: Amend CRZ rules to permit sand mining: Goa CM to Centre
news.para: Chief minister Pramod Sawant in a letter to the Union minister Bhupender Yadav said, “My state is facing an issue with regard to extraction of sand as the sand is only available in the estuarine stretches of the rivers.

news.title: Bengaluru: BDA's proposal to mortgage corner sites in Nadaprabhu Kempegowda opposed
news.para: The Nadaprabhu Kempegowda Layout Open Forum (NKLOF) wrote a letter to Chief Minister Siddaramaiah on April 6, appealing to him to direct the BDA to utilise the funds generated by mortgaging the corner vacant sites.

news.title: Spain to scrap 'golden visas' for foreign real estate investors
news.para: The programme awards non-EU citizens investing at least 500,000 euros ($541,250) - without taking out a mortgage - in Spanish real estate a special permit, allowing them to live and work in the country for three years.

news.title: Blackstone to take Apartment Income REIT private in $10 billion deal
news.para: Under the deal, Blackstone will pay $39.12 for each share of the real estate investment trust, representing a premium of about 25% to its closing price on Friday. Shares of the REIT jumped about 23%.

news.title: Gurugram: Five buildings of Chintels Paradiso to be brought down
news.para: DC Nishant Yadav grants permission for demolition of unsafe towers in Chintels Paradiso. Edifice Engineering will conduct floor-by-floor demolition. Safety measures, progress reports, and settlement agreements with flat owners are in place.

news.title: Aadhar Housing Finance receives Sebi’s nod for Rs 5,000 crore IPO
news.para: Aadhar Housing Finance, which filed preliminary IPO papers with the markets regulator in February, has obtained its observation on April 5, an update with the Securities and Exchange Board of India (Sebi) showed.
